cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on creating a database of video clips captured by driving recorders and developing a near-miss recognition method using computer vision techniques. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of automated systems in detecting near-miss incidents. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are possible categories as the paper mentions parameter fine-tuning and the development of a near-miss recognition method using machine learning techniques. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the importance of learning from near-miss incidents to improve driving safety.
